benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/allCustomFields - Retrieve account customFields

covered: GET Method - Valid Request: TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05 validate successful retrieval with various filters; TC06 covers empty data; TC11/TC25/TC26 touch performance aspects under load; TC09/TC21 cover audit enum handling; TC12-TC13 cover invalid/non-existent account scenarios; TC14-TC15 cover authorization cases; TC16, TC23 cover service/integration downtime scenarios; TC10/TC18/TC32 cover invalid/edge inputs and unsupported parameters; TC17, TC19, TC20 cover retry/timeout behaviors; TC24 ensures data consistency across services; TC27-TC29 cover edge/capacity scenarios; TC30-TC31 confirm edge-case pagination-like limits and partial inputs; TC33-TC36 cover extreme input edge cases; TC37-TC39 address accessibility and recovery
gaps: Pagination: No explicit tests for proper pagination (page size, page tokens) when returning large lists of custom fields.
Rate Limiting: No tests validating behavior under rate limiting or burst traffic.
Caching Behavior: No tests verifying caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or cache-related validation.
Explicit 2xx behavior for mixed parameter combinations beyond those covered (e.g., combinations not explicitly enumerated).
recommendations: Add explicit pagination-related scenarios (e.g., multiple pages, page size limits, and page navigation) to ensure scalable retrieval for large datasets.
Add tests for rate limiting/throttling behavior and proper 429 handling if applicable.
Add tests to validate caching headers and behaviors (ETag, Cache-Control) and validates conditional requests.
Consider adding targeted tests for mixed parameter edge cases not yet detailed (additional objectType/audit combos) to ensure consistent behavior.
